HB 346 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Schamerhorn
Redesignates the portion of the U.S. Hwy. 171 from La. Hwy. 118 to Sandra Ln. in the
village of Florien, La. as the "Speaker Joe R. Salter Memorial Highway".
Directs the Dept. of Transportation and Development (DOTD) or its contractors to erect and
maintain appropriate signage reflecting this designation provided local or private monies are
received by the DOTD equal to its actual costs for material, fabrication, mounting posts, and
installation of the signage, not to exceed the sum of $750 per sign.
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Add the middle initial "R." to the "Speaker Joe Salter Memorial Highway"
designation.
